==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Overglaze
<hw>O"ver*glaze`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Ceramics)</fld>
<sd>(a)</sd> <def>Applied over the glaze; -- said of enamel paintings,
which sometimes are seen to project from the surface of the ware.</def>
<sd>(b)</sd> <def>Suitable for applying upon the glaze; -- said of
vitrifiable colors used in ceramic decoration.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Overglide</ent>⟦br⟧
